    "breadcrumb": "Welcome",
    "content": "Friends: bybanshee.com Homepage from my sister, she is a digital artis. I love the style, make sure to check it!\nSecBSD This is the SecBSD Unix distribution, single handedly crafted by my brother purplerain. Incredible effort, really love the idea to habe a rocksold pentesting distribution.\nNotable Projects and Blogs Reverse Engineering for Beginners Not just for beginners, also good when you want to learn something new. Dennis is one of the Best guys out there. Very approachable when you have reversing questions.\nGwern Branwen’s blog Pseudonymous polymath’s blog exploring AI, security, darknet markets, and computational theory with obsessive rigor and extensive research. Essential for understanding the intersection of exploit development, machine learning, and weird machines.\nOpenBSD Security-focused operating system prioritizing correctness and proactive defense over performance. Known for hardened kernel, secure defaults, extensive code audits, and mitigations like ASLR, DEP, and stack canaries that became industry standard. Essential for understanding modern OS-level exploit defenses.",
